HEADWORD: Bolthead
<hw>Bolt"head`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A long, straight-necked, glass vessel for
chemical distillations; -- called also a <altname>matrass</altname> or
receiver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The head of a bolt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bolting</ent>⟦br⟧
